[US] SESSION & TOKEN SECURITY AUTOMATED CHECK — supplementary to [U] Session & Token Security
  This is a lightweight automated supplement to check [U]. It does NOT
  replace the full LLM adversarial review in [U].

  1. Search source code for token handling patterns:
     - JWT tokens stored in localStorage → flag (should be httpOnly cookie)
     - Token values in console.log or error messages → flag
     - Tokens sent in URL query parameters → flag

  2. Verify cookie configuration:
     - HttpOnly flag set on session cookies
     - Secure flag set on session cookies (for production)
     - SameSite attribute configured (Strict or Lax)

  3. Verify token validation:
     - alg: none attack is rejected (token with "alg":"none" → 401)
     - Token expiry is checked before acceptance
     - Refresh tokens are rotated on use

  For each item: PASS, FAIL, or N/A.
  For every FAIL: fix the issue. Do not proceed until all PASS or N/A.

  Print: "SESSION & TOKEN SECURITY AUTOMATED: [N] checks passed, [N] issues fixed"
